Definitions and terminology
KSE is a learning-focused project designed to explore modern game engine workflows, rendering systems, and editor tooling.

Introduction
KSE (KingStudio Engine) is a hybrid 2D/3D game engine project created to expand technical knowledge in software engineering, rendering, and game development.

Project Overview
KSE is a fast-paced game engine and development environment designed to support 2D and 3D gameplay, online features, and secure data handling.

Focus Areas
Client requirements and research
Security and data protection
2D and 3D programming
Online systems and networking
Engine architecture and rendering
Editor tools and UI design
